<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="116" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,946,1707]" box="[714,859,946,971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,946,1707]" box="[714,767,978,1003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis box="[714,767,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,946,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Wing length 0.81 (0.81-0.82, n = 5) mm, breadth 0.32 (n = 5) mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,946,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,783,1074,1099]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Head.</emphasis>
Dark brown. Vertex with six setae. Eyes bare, narrowly separated. Antennal plume brown. Maxillary palpus (
<figureCitation box="[920,1006,1138,1163]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1488,1505]" captionTargetBox="[216,1199,244,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-275@2.[216,1199,244,1466]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Alluaudomyia debilipenis n. sp.,; A, maxillary palpus; B, legs; C, hind tibial comb; D, wing; E, genitalia; F, parameres. Scale bars: A, 0.05 mm; D, 0.4 mm; E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396098/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) dark brown, pubescent and five-segmented, segment III elongated with small sub-apical sensory pits having three sensilla; segment V equal in length to segment III; length ratio of palpomeres I-V 3: 7: 9: 7: 9; PR 2.3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,946,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,803,1330,1355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Thorax.</emphasis>
Brown to dark brown. Scutum medially and laterally brown with submedian dark brown vitae; prescutellar area and humeral area large and pale; scutellum pale brown; post scutellum dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[714,1247,946,1707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,890,1490,1515]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[786,874,1490,1515]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="2.[151,162,1488,1505]" captionTargetBox="[216,1199,244,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-275@2.[216,1199,244,1466]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIG. 1. — Alluaudomyia debilipenis n. sp.,; A, maxillary palpus; B, legs; C, hind tibial comb; D, wing; E, genitalia; F, parameres. Scale bars: A, 0.05 mm; D, 0.4 mm; E, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396098/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Pale with brown bands; coxae and trochanters brown; fore and hind femora pale yellowish with subapical, median dark bands, mid femora with apical and median bands; all tibiae with apical, median and subbasal bands; fore and mid basitarsi pale but hind tarsomere I dark brown, rest of tar-
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
